Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Minsur, Southern Copper, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y   a n d   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-05-24T21:11:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/peru-stocks-buenaventura-cerro-verde-southern-copper-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index rose 1.4 percent to 21,776.94. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 1.5 percent to 2,800.94.  Gold miners gained as futures rose in  London  on concern
about  Europe ’s deepening sovereign debt crisis, said SAB
Inteligo analyst Daniel Mori.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration
company, jumped 4.5 percent to $2.33.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  ,
a U.K. minerals explorer with a gold mine in Peru, rose 4
percent to $1.30. Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the
country’s biggest precious-metals miner, advanced for a seventh
day, adding 1.2 percent to $41.70.  Copper and zinc producers rose as Goldman Sachs Group Inc.
advised investors to buy the metals, saying some markets with
supply constraints will tighten in the second half on economic
growth.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
producer, climbed 3.1 percent to 3.36 soles.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1
PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin producer, gained 3.1 percent
to 3.97 soles after tin rebounded in London.  Southern Copper
Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper producer, rose 3.1
percent to $34.95.  To contact the reporters on this story:
